title: SA records fourth coronavirus death, as 750 Qantas staff ordered to self-isolate
description: An Adelaide man dies from COVID-19 in the Royal Adelaide Hospital, becoming the fourth person in the state to die from the virus.
content:
Updated 
April 12, 2020 16:16:25
A fourth South Australian has died from COVID-19, while 750 Qantas staff have been ordered to self-isolate due to a cluster of cases at Adelaide Airport.
